  "summary": "Install-time host reconnaissance with DNS exfiltration to OAST collector",
  "details": "Package ships a preinstall hook (`\"preinstall\": \"node src/index.js \u003e /dev/null 2\u003e\u00261\"`) and a PoC payload at src/poc/index.js that shells out via child_process.exec to collect installer host identifiers (hostname, cwd, whoami) plus the installer's public IP fetched from ifconfig.me, then exfiltrates the concatenated data via nslookup DNS queries to an attacker-controlled subdomain of oast.site (d9bd62bu6g119svvav70o3p9tymtrxkoj.oast.site). oast.site is an interactsh out-of-band collector; the unique subdomain uniquely tags this installer to the campaign operator. The package identifies itself as a test/PoC with no legitimate functionality.",
